Jambo, I am Erick Lumunge
lumunge is a software developer located in nairobi, kenya with 3 years developing software from simple 'hello world' programs to complex ecommerce systems web applications. He has a background in computer science and loves sports such as cycling and football
The internet is the greatest reward to mankind as it offers us a wide range of choices and opportunities in contrast to outdated conventional ways where a group controlled what we know or do. This is my inspiration to being a developer because i can build anything i want. Software that makes a real impact in peoples lives from blogs the shares awesome stories to inspire people in the morning as they get to work to an ecommerce website that allows people to shop at the conveniece of their homes to health systems that advices users on their health status for free imporoving the quality of life of people the search engines that save us years of college to social media that connects people. Life was meant to be easy and the internet has proved that. Conventional eductaion did not serve me as i expected, I failed terribly in school in topic like history, biology, chemistry and this impacted my view on life but this all changed when i joined college and pursued what i liked, Computer Science. I started excelling to the point where i discovered that doing what you love makes success a joke and life a game so i have been playing ever since back in 2018. I dived into deeper computer science topics which intoduced me to code, the primary factor that all technolgy is built upon and l loved code ever since.
